    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomic revision of Muhlenbergia (Poaceae, Chloridoideae, Cynodonteae, Muhlenbergiinae) in Central America: phylogeny and classification" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure11>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure1> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure11>
    dc:description "Figure 11. A-E Muhlenbergia microsperma (DC.) Kunth A habit B inflorescence C ligule D glumes E floret F-J Muhlenbergia ligularis (Hack.) Hitchc. F habit G ligule H glumes I floret J stamens and pistil. A-E drawn from P. M. Peterson 4185 (US, WS) F-J drawn from P. M. Peterson, C. R. Annable, S. Laegaard & R. J. Soreng 12684 (US- 3275569)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/887879" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. A, B Bayesian tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in bold occur in Central America; Scale bar: 2 %." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/887869" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

